232 /// Create a block, using the current location context if no locations are
233 /// specified.
234 static MlirBlock createBlock(const nb::sequence &pyArgTypes,
235  const std::optional<nb::sequence> &pyArgLocs) {
236  SmallVector<MlirType> argTypes;
237  argTypes.reserve(nb::len(pyArgTypes));
238  for (const auto &pyType : pyArgTypes)
239  argTypes.push_back(nb::cast<PyType &>(pyType));
240 
241  SmallVector<MlirLocation> argLocs;
242  if (pyArgLocs) {
243  argLocs.reserve(nb::len(*pyArgLocs));
244  for (const auto &pyLoc : *pyArgLocs)
245  argLocs.push_back(nb::cast<PyLocation &>(pyLoc));
246  } else if (!argTypes.empty()) {
247  argLocs.assign(argTypes.size(), DefaultingPyLocation::resolve());
248  }
249 
250  if (argTypes.size() != argLocs.size())
251  throw nb::value_error(("Expected " + Twine(argTypes.size()) +
252  " locations, got: " + Twine(argLocs.size()))
253  .str()
254  .c_str());
255  return mlirBlockCreate(argTypes.size(), argTypes.data(), argLocs.data());
256 }

339 class PyRegionIterator {
340 public:
341  PyRegionIterator(PyOperationRef operation)
342  : operation(std::move(operation)) {}
343 
344  PyRegionIterator &dunderIter() { return *this; }
345 
346  PyRegion dunderNext() {
347  operation->checkValid();
348  if (nextIndex >= mlirOperationGetNumRegions(operation->get())) {
349  throw nb::stop_iteration();
350  }
351  MlirRegion region = mlirOperationGetRegion(operation->get(), nextIndex++);
352  return PyRegion(operation, region);
353  }

356  nb::class_<PyRegionIterator>(m, "RegionIterator")
357  .def("__iter__", &PyRegionIterator::dunderIter)
358  .def("__next__", &PyRegionIterator::dunderNext);
359  }
360 
361 private:
362  PyOperationRef operation;
363  int nextIndex = 0;
364 };

439 /// Blocks are exposed by the C-API as a forward-only linked list. In Python,
440 /// we present them as a more full-featured list-like container but optimize
441 /// it for forward iteration. Blocks are always owned by a region.
442 class PyBlockList {
443 public:
444  PyBlockList(PyOperationRef operation, MlirRegion region)
445  : operation(std::move(operation)), region(region) {}
446 
447  PyBlockIterator dunderIter() {
448  operation->checkValid();
449  return PyBlockIterator(operation, mlirRegionGetFirstBlock(region));
450  }
451 
452  intptr_t dunderLen() {
453  operation->checkValid();
454  intptr_t count = 0;
455  MlirBlock block = mlirRegionGetFirstBlock(region);
456  while (!mlirBlockIsNull(block)) {
457  count += 1;
458  block = mlirBlockGetNextInRegion(block);
459  }
460  return count;
461  }
462 
463  PyBlock dunderGetItem(intptr_t index) {
464  operation->checkValid();
465  if (index < 0) {
466  index += dunderLen();
467  }
468  if (index < 0) {
469  throw nb::index_error("attempt to access out of bounds block");
470  }
471  MlirBlock block = mlirRegionGetFirstBlock(region);
472  while (!mlirBlockIsNull(block)) {
473  if (index == 0) {
474  return PyBlock(operation, block);
475  }
476  block = mlirBlockGetNextInRegion(block);
477  index -= 1;
478  }
479  throw nb::index_error("attempt to access out of bounds block");
480  }
481 
482  PyBlock appendBlock(const nb::args &pyArgTypes,
483  const std::optional<nb::sequence> &pyArgLocs) {
484  operation->checkValid();
485  MlirBlock block =
486  createBlock(nb::cast<nb::sequence>(pyArgTypes), pyArgLocs);
487  mlirRegionAppendOwnedBlock(region, block);
488  return PyBlock(operation, block);
489  }
490 
491  static void bind(nb::module_ &m) {
492  nb::class_<PyBlockList>(m, "BlockList")
493  .def("__getitem__", &PyBlockList::dunderGetItem)
494  .def("__iter__", &PyBlockList::dunderIter)
495  .def("__len__", &PyBlockList::dunderLen)
496  .def("append", &PyBlockList::appendBlock, kAppendBlockDocstring,
497  nb::arg("args"), nb::kw_only(),
498  nb::arg("arg_locs") = std::nullopt);
499  }
500 
501 private:
502  PyOperationRef operation;
503  MlirRegion region;
504 };

536 /// Operations are exposed by the C-API as a forward-only linked list. In
537 /// Python, we present them as a more full-featured list-like container but
538 /// optimize it for forward iteration. Iterable operations are always owned
539 /// by a block.
540 class PyOperationList {
541 public:
542  PyOperationList(PyOperationRef parentOperation, MlirBlock block)
543  : parentOperation(std::move(parentOperation)), block(block) {}
544 
545  PyOperationIterator dunderIter() {
546  parentOperation->checkValid();
547  return PyOperationIterator(parentOperation,
548  mlirBlockGetFirstOperation(block));
549  }
550 
551  intptr_t dunderLen() {
552  parentOperation->checkValid();
553  intptr_t count = 0;
554  MlirOperation childOp = mlirBlockGetFirstOperation(block);
555  while (!mlirOperationIsNull(childOp)) {
556  count += 1;
557  childOp = mlirOperationGetNextInBlock(childOp);
558  }
559  return count;
560  }
561 
562  nb::object dunderGetItem(intptr_t index) {
563  parentOperation->checkValid();
564  if (index < 0) {
565  index += dunderLen();
566  }
567  if (index < 0) {
568  throw nb::index_error("attempt to access out of bounds operation");
569  }
570  MlirOperation childOp = mlirBlockGetFirstOperation(block);
571  while (!mlirOperationIsNull(childOp)) {
572  if (index == 0) {
573  return PyOperation::forOperation(parentOperation->getContext(), childOp)
574  ->createOpView();
575  }
576  childOp = mlirOperationGetNextInBlock(childOp);
577  index -= 1;
578  }
579  throw nb::index_error("attempt to access out of bounds operation");
580  }
581 
582  static void bind(nb::module_ &m) {
583  nb::class_<PyOperationList>(m, "OperationList")
584  .def("__getitem__", &PyOperationList::dunderGetItem)
585  .def("__iter__", &PyOperationList::dunderIter)
586  .def("__len__", &PyOperationList::dunderLen);
587  }
588 
589 private:
590  PyOperationRef parentOperation;
591  MlirBlock block;
592 };

655 PyMlirContext::~PyMlirContext() {
656  // Note that the only public way to construct an instance is via the
657  // forContext method, which always puts the associated handle into
658  // liveContexts.
659  nb::gil_scoped_acquire acquire;
660  {

662  getLiveContexts().erase(context.ptr);

665 }

671 nb::object PyMlirContext::createFromCapsule(nb::object capsule) {
672  MlirContext rawContext = mlirPythonCapsuleToContext(capsule.ptr());
673  if (mlirContextIsNull(rawContext))
674  throw nb::python_error();
675  return forContext(rawContext).releaseObject();

678 PyMlirContextRef PyMlirContext::forContext(MlirContext context) {
679  nb::gil_scoped_acquire acquire;
680  nb::ft_lock_guard lock(live_contexts_mutex);
681  auto &liveContexts = getLiveContexts();
682  auto it = liveContexts.find(context.ptr);
683  if (it == liveContexts.end()) {
684  // Create.
685  PyMlirContext *unownedContextWrapper = new PyMlirContext(context);
686  nb::object pyRef = nb::cast(unownedContextWrapper);
687  assert(pyRef && "cast to nb::object failed");
688  liveContexts[context.ptr] = unownedContextWrapper;
689  return PyMlirContextRef(unownedContextWrapper, std::move(pyRef));
690  }
691  // Use existing.
692  nb::object pyRef = nb::cast(it->second);
693  return PyMlirContextRef(it->second, std::move(pyRef));
694 }

721 size_t PyMlirContext::clearLiveOperations() {
722

726  std::swap(operations, liveOperations);

734 void PyMlirContext::clearOperation(MlirOperation op) {
735  PyOperation *py_op;
736  {
737  nb::ft_lock_guard lock(liveOperationsMutex);
738  auto it = liveOperations.find(op.ptr);
739  if (it == liveOperations.end()) {
740  return;
741  }
742  py_op = it->second.second;
743  liveOperations.erase(it);
744  }
745  py_op->setInvalid();
746 }

748 void PyMlirContext::clearOperationsInside(PyOperationBase &op) {
749  typedef struct {
750  PyOperation &rootOp;
751  bool rootSeen;
752  } callBackData;
753  callBackData data{op.getOperation(), false};
754  // Mark all ops below the op that the passmanager will be rooted
755  // at (but not op itself - note the preorder) as invalid.
756  MlirOperationWalkCallback invalidatingCallback = [](MlirOperation op,
757  void *userData) {
758  callBackData *data = static_cast<callBackData *>(userData);
759  if (LLVM_LIKELY(data->rootSeen))
760  data->rootOp.getOperation().getContext()->clearOperation(op);
761  else
762  data->rootSeen = true;
763  return MlirWalkResult::MlirWalkResultAdvance;
764  };
765  mlirOperationWalk(op.getOperation(), invalidatingCallback,
766  static_cast<void *>(&data), MlirWalkPreOrder);
767 }
768 void PyMlirContext::clearOperationsInside(MlirOperation op) {
769  PyOperationRef opRef = PyOperation::forOperation(getRef(), op);
770  clearOperationsInside(opRef->getOperation());
771 }

773 void PyMlirContext::clearOperationAndInside(PyOperationBase &op) {
774  MlirOperationWalkCallback invalidatingCallback = [](MlirOperation op,
775  void *userData) {
776  PyMlirContextRef &contextRef = *static_cast<PyMlirContextRef *>(userData);
777  contextRef->clearOperation(op);
778  return MlirWalkResult::MlirWalkResultAdvance;
779  };
780  mlirOperationWalk(op.getOperation(), invalidatingCallback,
781  &op.getOperation().getContext(), MlirWalkPreOrder);
782 }

796 nb::object PyMlirContext::attachDiagnosticHandler(nb::object callback) {
797  // Note that ownership is transferred to the delete callback below by way of
798  // an explicit inc_ref (borrow).
799  PyDiagnosticHandler *pyHandler =
800  new PyDiagnosticHandler(get(), std::move(callback));
801  nb::object pyHandlerObject =
802  nb::cast(pyHandler, nb::rv_policy::take_ownership);
803  pyHandlerObject.inc_ref();
804 
805  // In these C callbacks, the userData is a PyDiagnosticHandler* that is
806  // guaranteed to be known to pybind.
807  auto handlerCallback =
808  +[](MlirDiagnostic diagnostic, void *userData) -> MlirLogicalResult {
809  PyDiagnostic *pyDiagnostic = new PyDiagnostic(diagnostic);
810  nb::object pyDiagnosticObject =
811  nb::cast(pyDiagnostic, nb::rv_policy::take_ownership);
812 
813  auto *pyHandler = static_cast<PyDiagnosticHandler *>(userData);
814  bool result = false;
815  {
816  // Since this can be called from arbitrary C++ contexts, always get the
817  // gil.
818  nb::gil_scoped_acquire gil;
819  try {
820  result = nb::cast<bool>(pyHandler->callback(pyDiagnostic));
821  } catch (std::exception &e) {
822  fprintf(stderr, "MLIR Python Diagnostic handler raised exception: %s\n",
823  e.what());
824  pyHandler->hadError = true;
825  }
826  }
827 
828  pyDiagnostic->invalidate();
829  return result ? mlirLogicalResultSuccess() : mlirLogicalResultFailure();
830  };
831  auto deleteCallback = +[](void *userData) {
832  auto *pyHandler = static_cast<PyDiagnosticHandler *>(userData);
833  assert(pyHandler->registeredID && "handler is not registered");
834  pyHandler->registeredID.reset();
835 
836  // Decrement reference, balancing the inc_ref() above.
837  nb::object pyHandlerObject = nb::cast(pyHandler, nb::rv_policy::reference);
838  pyHandlerObject.dec_ref();
839  };
840 
841  pyHandler->registeredID = mlirContextAttachDiagnosticHandler(
842  get(), handlerCallback, static_cast<void *>(pyHandler), deleteCallback);
843  return pyHandlerObject;
844 }
845 
846 MlirLogicalResult PyMlirContext::ErrorCapture::handler(MlirDiagnostic diag,
847  void *userData) {
848  auto *self = static_cast<ErrorCapture *>(userData);
849  // Check if the context requested we emit errors instead of capturing them.
850  if (self->ctx->emitErrorDiagnostics)
851  return mlirLogicalResultFailure();
852 
853  if (mlirDiagnosticGetSeverity(diag) != MlirDiagnosticError)
854  return mlirLogicalResultFailure();
855 
856  self->errors.emplace_back(PyDiagnostic(diag).getInfo());
857  return mlirLogicalResultSuccess();
858 }

887 void PyThreadContextEntry::push(FrameKind frameKind, nb::object context,
888  nb::object insertionPoint,
889  nb::object location) {
890  auto &stack = getStack();
891  stack.emplace_back(frameKind, std::move(context), std::move(insertionPoint),
892  std::move(location));
893  // If the new stack has more than one entry and the context of the new top
894  // entry matches the previous, copy the insertionPoint and location from the
895  // previous entry if missing from the new top entry.
896  if (stack.size() > 1) {
897  auto &prev = *(stack.rbegin() + 1);
898  auto &current = stack.back();
899  if (current.context.is(prev.context)) {
900  // Default non-context objects from the previous entry.
901  if (!current.insertionPoint)
902  current.insertionPoint = prev.insertionPoint;
903  if (!current.location)
904  current.location = prev.location;
905  }
906  }
907 }

949 void PyThreadContextEntry::popContext(PyMlirContext &context) {
950  auto &stack = getStack();
951  if (stack.empty())
952  throw std::runtime_error("Unbalanced Context enter/exit");
953  auto &tos = stack.back();

955  throw std::runtime_error("Unbalanced Context enter/exit");

957 }

1157 PyModule::~PyModule() {
1158  nb::gil_scoped_acquire acquire;
1159  auto &liveModules = getContext()->liveModules;
1160  assert(liveModules.count(module.ptr) == 1 &&

1166 PyModuleRef PyModule::forModule(MlirModule module) {
1167  MlirContext context = mlirModuleGetContext(module);
1168  PyMlirContextRef contextRef = PyMlirContext::forContext(context);
1169 
1170  nb::gil_scoped_acquire acquire;
1171  auto &liveModules = contextRef->liveModules;
1172  auto it = liveModules.find(module.ptr);
1173  if (it == liveModules.end()) {
1174  // Create.
1175  PyModule *unownedModule = new PyModule(std::move(contextRef), module);
1176  // Note that the default return value policy on cast is automatic_reference,
1177  // which does not take ownership (delete will not be called).
1178  // Just be explicit.
1179  nb::object pyRef = nb::cast(unownedModule, nb::rv_policy::take_ownership);
1180  unownedModule->handle = pyRef;
1181  liveModules[module.ptr] =
1182  std::make_pair(unownedModule->handle, unownedModule);
1183  return PyModuleRef(unownedModule, std::move(pyRef));
1184  }
1185  // Use existing.
1186  PyModule *existing = it->second.second;
1187  nb::object pyRef = nb::borrow<nb::object>(it->second.first);
1188  return PyModuleRef(existing, std::move(pyRef));
1189 }

1209 PyOperation::~PyOperation() {
1210  // If the operation has already been invalidated there is nothing to do.
1211  if (!valid)
1212  return;
1213 
1214  // Otherwise, invalidate the operation and remove it from live map when it is
1215  // attached.
1216  if (isAttached()) {
1217  getContext()->clearOperation(*this);
1218  } else {
1219  // And destroy it when it is detached, i.e. owned by Python, in which case
1220  // all nested operations must be invalidated at removed from the live map as
1221  // well.
1222  erase();
1223  }
1224 }

1228 // Constructs a new object of type T in-place on the Python heap, returning a
1229 // PyObjectRef to it, loosely analogous to std::make_shared<T>().
1230 template <typename T, class... Args>
1231 PyObjectRef<T> makeObjectRef(Args &&...args) {
1232  nb::handle type = nb::type<T>();
1233  nb::object instance = nb::inst_alloc(type);
1234  T *ptr = nb::inst_ptr<T>(instance);
1235  new (ptr) T(std::forward<Args>(args)...);
1236  nb::inst_mark_ready(instance);
1237  return PyObjectRef<T>(ptr, std::move(instance));
1238 }

1242 PyOperationRef PyOperation::createInstance(PyMlirContextRef contextRef,
1243  MlirOperation operation,
1244  nb::object parentKeepAlive) {
1245  // Create.
1246  PyOperationRef unownedOperation =
1247  makeObjectRef<PyOperation>(std::move(contextRef), operation);
1248  unownedOperation->handle = unownedOperation.getObject();
1249  if (parentKeepAlive) {
1250  unownedOperation->parentKeepAlive = std::move(parentKeepAlive);
1251  }
1252  return unownedOperation;
1253 }

1255 PyOperationRef PyOperation::forOperation(PyMlirContextRef contextRef,
1256  MlirOperation operation,
1257  nb::object parentKeepAlive) {
1258  nb::ft_lock_guard lock(contextRef->liveOperationsMutex);
1259  auto &liveOperations = contextRef->liveOperations;
1260  auto it = liveOperations.find(operation.ptr);
1261  if (it == liveOperations.end()) {
1262  // Create.
1263  PyOperationRef result = createInstance(std::move(contextRef), operation,
1264  std::move(parentKeepAlive));
1265  liveOperations[operation.ptr] =
1266  std::make_pair(result.getObject(), result.get());
1267  return result;
1268  }
1269  // Use existing.
1270  PyOperation *existing = it->second.second;
1271  nb::object pyRef = nb::borrow<nb::object>(it->second.first);
1272  return PyOperationRef(existing, std::move(pyRef));
1273 }

1275 PyOperationRef PyOperation::createDetached(PyMlirContextRef contextRef,
1276  MlirOperation operation,
1277  nb::object parentKeepAlive) {
1278  nb::ft_lock_guard lock(contextRef->liveOperationsMutex);
1279  auto &liveOperations = contextRef->liveOperations;
1280  assert(liveOperations.count(operation.ptr) == 0 &&
1281  "cannot create detached operation that already exists");
1282  (void)liveOperations;
1283  PyOperationRef created = createInstance(std::move(contextRef), operation,
1284  std::move(parentKeepAlive));
1285  liveOperations[operation.ptr] =
1286  std::make_pair(created.getObject(), created.get());
1287  created->attached = false;
1288  return created;
1289 }

1379 void PyOperationBase::walk(
1380  std::function<MlirWalkResult(MlirOperation)> callback,
1381  MlirWalkOrder walkOrder) {
1382  PyOperation &operation = getOperation();
1383  operation.checkValid();
1384  struct UserData {
1385  std::function<MlirWalkResult(MlirOperation)> callback;
1386  bool gotException;
1387  std::string exceptionWhat;
1388  nb::object exceptionType;
1389  };
1390  UserData userData{callback, false, {}, {}};
1391  MlirOperationWalkCallback walkCallback = [](MlirOperation op,
1392  void *userData) {
1393  UserData *calleeUserData = static_cast<UserData *>(userData);
1394  try {
1395  return (calleeUserData->callback)(op);
1396  } catch (nb::python_error &e) {
1397  calleeUserData->gotException = true;
1398  calleeUserData->exceptionWhat = std::string(e.what());
1399  calleeUserData->exceptionType = nb::borrow(e.type());
1400  return MlirWalkResult::MlirWalkResultInterrupt;
1401  }
1402  };
1403  mlirOperationWalk(operation, walkCallback, &userData, walkOrder);
1404  if (userData.gotException) {
1405  std::string message("Exception raised in callback: ");
1406  message.append(userData.exceptionWhat);
1407  throw std::runtime_error(message);
1408  }
1409 }

1521 nb::object PyOperation::create(std::string_view name,
1522  std::optional<std::vector<PyType *>> results,
1523  llvm::ArrayRef<MlirValue> operands,
1524  std::optional<nb::dict> attributes,
1525  std::optional<std::vector<PyBlock *>> successors,
1526  int regions, DefaultingPyLocation location,
1527  const nb::object &maybeIp, bool inferType) {
1528  llvm::SmallVector<MlirType, 4> mlirResults;
1529  llvm::SmallVector<MlirBlock, 4> mlirSuccessors;
1530  llvm::SmallVector<std::pair<std::string, MlirAttribute>, 4> mlirAttributes;
1531 
1532  // General parameter validation.
1533  if (regions < 0)
1534  throw nb::value_error("number of regions must be >= 0");
1535 
1536  // Unpack/validate results.
1537  if (results) {
1538  mlirResults.reserve(results->size());
1539  for (PyType *result : *results) {
1540  // TODO: Verify result type originate from the same context.
1541  if (!result)
1542  throw nb::value_error("result type cannot be None");
1543  mlirResults.push_back(*result);
1544  }
1545  }
1546  // Unpack/validate attributes.
1547  if (attributes) {
1548  mlirAttributes.reserve(attributes->size());
1549  for (std::pair<nb::handle, nb::handle> it : *attributes) {
1550  std::string key;
1551  try {
1552  key = nb::cast<std::string>(it.first);
1553  } catch (nb::cast_error &err) {
1554  std::string msg = "Invalid attribute key (not a string) when "
1555  "attempting to create the operation \"" +
1556  std::string(name) + "\" (" + err.what() + ")";
1557  throw nb::type_error(msg.c_str());
1558  }
1559  try {
1560  auto &attribute = nb::cast<PyAttribute &>(it.second);
1561  // TODO: Verify attribute originates from the same context.
1562  mlirAttributes.emplace_back(std::move(key), attribute);
1563  } catch (nb::cast_error &err) {
1564  std::string msg = "Invalid attribute value for the key \"" + key +
1565  "\" when attempting to create the operation \"" +
1566  std::string(name) + "\" (" + err.what() + ")";
1567  throw nb::type_error(msg.c_str());
1568  } catch (std::runtime_error &) {
1569  // This exception seems thrown when the value is "None".
1570  std::string msg =
1571  "Found an invalid (`None`?) attribute value for the key \"" + key +
1572  "\" when attempting to create the operation \"" +
1573  std::string(name) + "\"";
1574  throw std::runtime_error(msg);
1575  }
1576  }
1577  }
1578  // Unpack/validate successors.
1579  if (successors) {
1580  mlirSuccessors.reserve(successors->size());
1581  for (auto *successor : *successors) {
1582  // TODO: Verify successor originate from the same context.
1583  if (!successor)
1584  throw nb::value_error("successor block cannot be None");
1585  mlirSuccessors.push_back(successor->get());
1586  }
1587  }
1588 
1589  // Apply unpacked/validated to the operation state. Beyond this
1590  // point, exceptions cannot be thrown or else the state will leak.
1591  MlirOperationState state =
1592  mlirOperationStateGet(toMlirStringRef(name), location);
1593  if (!operands.empty())
1594  mlirOperationStateAddOperands(&state, operands.size(), operands.data());
1595  state.enableResultTypeInference = inferType;
1596  if (!mlirResults.empty())
1597  mlirOperationStateAddResults(&state, mlirResults.size(),
1598  mlirResults.data());
1599  if (!mlirAttributes.empty()) {
1600  // Note that the attribute names directly reference bytes in
1601  // mlirAttributes, so that vector must not be changed from here
1602  // on.
1603  llvm::SmallVector<MlirNamedAttribute, 4> mlirNamedAttributes;
1604  mlirNamedAttributes.reserve(mlirAttributes.size());
1605  for (auto &it : mlirAttributes)
1606  mlirNamedAttributes.push_back(mlirNamedAttributeGet(
1607  mlirIdentifierGet(mlirAttributeGetContext(it.second),
1608  toMlirStringRef(it.first)),
1609  it.second));
1610  mlirOperationStateAddAttributes(&state, mlirNamedAttributes.size(),
1611  mlirNamedAttributes.data());
1612  }
1613  if (!mlirSuccessors.empty())
1614  mlirOperationStateAddSuccessors(&state, mlirSuccessors.size(),
1615  mlirSuccessors.data());
1616  if (regions) {
1617  llvm::SmallVector<MlirRegion, 4> mlirRegions;
1618  mlirRegions.resize(regions);
1619  for (int i = 0; i < regions; ++i)
1620  mlirRegions[i] = mlirRegionCreate();
1621  mlirOperationStateAddOwnedRegions(&state, mlirRegions.size(),
1622  mlirRegions.data());
1623  }
1624 
1625  // Construct the operation.
1626  MlirOperation operation = mlirOperationCreate(&state);
1627  if (!operation.ptr)
1628  throw nb::value_error("Operation creation failed");
1629  PyOperationRef created =
1630  PyOperation::createDetached(location->getContext(), operation);
1631  maybeInsertOperation(created, maybeIp);
1632 
1633  return created.getObject();
1634 }

1662 namespace {
1663 /// CRTP base class for Python MLIR values that subclass Value and should be
1664 /// castable from it. The value hierarchy is one level deep and is not supposed
1665 /// to accommodate other levels unless core MLIR changes.
1666 template <typename DerivedTy>
1667 class PyConcreteValue : public PyValue {
1668 public:
1669  // Derived classes must define statics for:
1670  // IsAFunctionTy isaFunction
1671  // const char *pyClassName
1672  // and redefine bindDerived.
1673  using ClassTy = nb::class_<DerivedTy, PyValue>;
1674  using IsAFunctionTy = bool (*)(MlirValue);
1675 
1676  PyConcreteValue() = default;
1677  PyConcreteValue(PyOperationRef operationRef, MlirValue value)
1678  : PyValue(operationRef, value) {}
1679  PyConcreteValue(PyValue &orig)
1680  : PyConcreteValue(orig.getParentOperation(), castFrom(orig)) {}
1681 
1682  /// Attempts to cast the original value to the derived type and throws on
1683  /// type mismatches.
1684  static MlirValue castFrom(PyValue &orig) {
1685  if (!DerivedTy::isaFunction(orig.get())) {
1686  auto origRepr = nb::cast<std::string>(nb::repr(nb::cast(orig)));
1687  throw nb::value_error((Twine("Cannot cast value to ") +
1688  DerivedTy::pyClassName + " (from " + origRepr +
1689  ")")
1690  .str()
1691  .c_str());
1692  }
1693  return orig.get();
1694  }
1695 
1696  /// Binds the Python module objects to functions of this class.
1697  static void bind(nb::module_ &m) {
1698  auto cls = ClassTy(m, DerivedTy::pyClassName);
1699  cls.def(nb::init<PyValue &>(), nb::keep_alive<0, 1>(), nb::arg("value"));
1700  cls.def_static(
1701  "isinstance",
1702  [](PyValue &otherValue) -> bool {
1703  return DerivedTy::isaFunction(otherValue);
1704  },
1705  nb::arg("other_value"));
1706  cls.def(MLIR_PYTHON_MAYBE_DOWNCAST_ATTR,
1707  [](DerivedTy &self) { return self.maybeDownCast(); });
1708  DerivedTy::bindDerived(cls);
1709  }
1710 
1711  /// Implemented by derived classes to add methods to the Python subclass.
1712  static void bindDerived(ClassTy &m) {}
1713 };
1714 
1715 } // namespace

1717 /// Python wrapper for MlirOpResult.
1718 class PyOpResult : public PyConcreteValue<PyOpResult> {
1719 public:
1720  static constexpr IsAFunctionTy isaFunction = mlirValueIsAOpResult;
1721  static constexpr const char *pyClassName = "OpResult";
1722  using PyConcreteValue::PyConcreteValue;

1724  static void bindDerived(ClassTy &c) {

1727  mlirOperationEqual(self.getParentOperation()->get(),
1728  mlirOpResultGetOwner(self.get())) &&

1730  return self.getParentOperation().getObject();
1731  });
1732  c.def_prop_ro("result_number", [](PyOpResult &self) {

1734  });

1738 /// Returns the list of types of the values held by container.

1741  PyMlirContextRef &context) {

1750 /// A list of operation results. Internally, these are stored as consecutive
1751 /// elements, random access is cheap. The (returned) result list is associated
1752 /// with the operation whose results these are, and thus extends the lifetime of
1753 /// this operation.
1754 class PyOpResultList : public Sliceable<PyOpResultList, PyOpResult> {
1755 public:
1756  static constexpr const char *pyClassName = "OpResultList";
1757  using SliceableT = Sliceable<PyOpResultList, PyOpResult>;
1758 
1759  PyOpResultList(PyOperationRef operation, intptr_t startIndex = 0,
1760  intptr_t length = -1, intptr_t step = 1)
1761  : Sliceable(startIndex,
1762  length == -1 ? mlirOperationGetNumResults(operation->get())
1763  : length,
1764  step),
1765  operation(std::move(operation)) {}
1766 
1767  static void bindDerived(ClassTy &c) {
1768  c.def_prop_ro("types", [](PyOpResultList &self) {
1769  return getValueTypes(self, self.operation->getContext());
1770  });
1771  c.def_prop_ro("owner", [](PyOpResultList &self) {
1772  return self.operation->createOpView();
1773  });
1774  }
1775 
1776  PyOperationRef &getOperation() { return operation; }
1777 
1778 private:
1779  /// Give the parent CRTP class access to hook implementations below.
1780  friend class Sliceable<PyOpResultList, PyOpResult>;
1781 
1782  intptr_t getRawNumElements() {
1783  operation->checkValid();
1784  return mlirOperationGetNumResults(operation->get());
1785  }
1786 
1787  PyOpResult getRawElement(intptr_t index) {
1788  PyValue value(operation, mlirOperationGetResult(operation->get(), index));
1789  return PyOpResult(value);
1790  }
1791 
1792  PyOpResultList slice(intptr_t startIndex, intptr_t length, intptr_t step) {
1793  return PyOpResultList(operation, startIndex, length, step);
1794  }
1795 
1796  PyOperationRef operation;
1797 };

1803 static void populateResultTypes(StringRef name, nb::list resultTypeList,
1804  const nb::object &resultSegmentSpecObj,
1805  std::vector<int32_t> &resultSegmentLengths,
1806  std::vector<PyType *> &resultTypes) {
1807  resultTypes.reserve(resultTypeList.size());
1808  if (resultSegmentSpecObj.is_none()) {
1809  // Non-variadic result unpacking.
1810  for (const auto &it : llvm::enumerate(resultTypeList)) {
1811  try {
1812  resultTypes.push_back(nb::cast<PyType *>(it.value()));
1813  if (!resultTypes.back())
1814  throw nb::cast_error();
1815  } catch (nb::cast_error &err) {
1816  throw nb::value_error((llvm::Twine("Result ") +
1817  llvm::Twine(it.index()) + " of operation \"" +
1818  name + "\" must be a Type (" + err.what() + ")")
1819  .str()
1820  .c_str());
1821  }
1822  }
1823  } else {
1824  // Sized result unpacking.
1825  auto resultSegmentSpec = nb::cast<std::vector<int>>(resultSegmentSpecObj);
1826  if (resultSegmentSpec.size() != resultTypeList.size()) {
1827  throw nb::value_error((llvm::Twine("Operation \"") + name +
1828  "\" requires " +
1829  llvm::Twine(resultSegmentSpec.size()) +
1830  " result segments but was provided " +
1831  llvm::Twine(resultTypeList.size()))
1832  .str()
1833  .c_str());
1834  }
1835  resultSegmentLengths.reserve(resultTypeList.size());
1836  for (const auto &it :
1837  llvm::enumerate(llvm::zip(resultTypeList, resultSegmentSpec))) {
1838  int segmentSpec = std::get<1>(it.value());
1839  if (segmentSpec == 1 || segmentSpec == 0) {
1840  // Unpack unary element.
1841  try {
1842  auto *resultType = nb::cast<PyType *>(std::get<0>(it.value()));
1843  if (resultType) {
1844  resultTypes.push_back(resultType);
1845  resultSegmentLengths.push_back(1);
1846  } else if (segmentSpec == 0) {
1847  // Allowed to be optional.
1848  resultSegmentLengths.push_back(0);
1849  } else {
1850  throw nb::value_error(
1851  (llvm::Twine("Result ") + llvm::Twine(it.index()) +
1852  " of operation \"" + name +
1853  "\" must be a Type (was None and result is not optional)")
1854  .str()
1855  .c_str());
1856  }
1857  } catch (nb::cast_error &err) {
1858  throw nb::value_error((llvm::Twine("Result ") +
1859  llvm::Twine(it.index()) + " of operation \"" +
1860  name + "\" must be a Type (" + err.what() +
1861  ")")
1862  .str()
1863  .c_str());
1864  }
1865  } else if (segmentSpec == -1) {
1866  // Unpack sequence by appending.
1867  try {
1868  if (std::get<0>(it.value()).is_none()) {
1869  // Treat it as an empty list.
1870  resultSegmentLengths.push_back(0);
1871  } else {
1872  // Unpack the list.
1873  auto segment = nb::cast<nb::sequence>(std::get<0>(it.value()));
1874  for (nb::handle segmentItem : segment) {
1875  resultTypes.push_back(nb::cast<PyType *>(segmentItem));
1876  if (!resultTypes.back()) {
1877  throw nb::type_error("contained a None item");
1878  }
1879  }
1880  resultSegmentLengths.push_back(nb::len(segment));
1881  }
1882  } catch (std::exception &err) {
1883  // NOTE: Sloppy to be using a catch-all here, but there are at least
1884  // three different unrelated exceptions that can be thrown in the
1885  // above "casts". Just keep the scope above small and catch them all.
1886  throw nb::value_error((llvm::Twine("Result ") +
1887  llvm::Twine(it.index()) + " of operation \"" +
1888  name + "\" must be a Sequence of Types (" +
1889  err.what() + ")")
1890  .str()
1891  .c_str());
1892  }
1893  } else {
1894  throw nb::value_error("Unexpected segment spec");
1895  }
1896  }
1897  }
1898 }
1899 
1900 static MlirValue getUniqueResult(MlirOperation operation) {
1901  auto numResults = mlirOperationGetNumResults(operation);
1902  if (numResults != 1) {
1903  auto name = mlirIdentifierStr(mlirOperationGetName(operation));
1904  throw nb::value_error((Twine("Cannot call .result on operation ") +
1905  StringRef(name.data, name.length) + " which has " +
1906  Twine(numResults) +
1907  " results (it is only valid for operations with a "
1908  "single result)")
1909  .str()
1910  .c_str());
1911  }
1912  return mlirOperationGetResult(operation, 0);
1913 }
1914 
1915 static MlirValue getOpResultOrValue(nb::handle operand) {
1916  if (operand.is_none()) {
1917  throw nb::value_error("contained a None item");
1918  }
1919  PyOperationBase *op;
1920  if (nb::try_cast<PyOperationBase *>(operand, op)) {
1921  return getUniqueResult(op->getOperation());
1922  }
1923  PyOpResultList *opResultList;
1924  if (nb::try_cast<PyOpResultList *>(operand, opResultList)) {
1925  return getUniqueResult(opResultList->getOperation()->get());
1926  }
1927  PyValue *value;
1928  if (nb::try_cast<PyValue *>(operand, value)) {
1929  return value->get();
1930  }
1931  throw nb::value_error("is not a Value");
1932 }

1934 nb::object PyOpView::buildGeneric(
1935  std::string_view name, std::tuple<int, bool> opRegionSpec,
1936  nb::object operandSegmentSpecObj, nb::object resultSegmentSpecObj,
1937  std::optional<nb::list> resultTypeList, nb::list operandList,
1938  std::optional<nb::dict> attributes,
1939  std::optional<std::vector<PyBlock *>> successors,
1940  std::optional<int> regions, DefaultingPyLocation location,
1941  const nb::object &maybeIp) {
1942  PyMlirContextRef context = location->getContext();
1943 
1944  // Class level operation construction metadata.
1945  // Operand and result segment specs are either none, which does no
1946  // variadic unpacking, or a list of ints with segment sizes, where each
1947  // element is either a positive number (typically 1 for a scalar) or -1 to
1948  // indicate that it is derived from the length of the same-indexed operand
1949  // or result (implying that it is a list at that position).
1950  std::vector<int32_t> operandSegmentLengths;
1951  std::vector<int32_t> resultSegmentLengths;
1952 
1953  // Validate/determine region count.
1954  int opMinRegionCount = std::get<0>(opRegionSpec);
1955  bool opHasNoVariadicRegions = std::get<1>(opRegionSpec);
1956  if (!regions) {
1957  regions = opMinRegionCount;
1958  }
1959  if (*regions < opMinRegionCount) {
1960  throw nb::value_error(
1961  (llvm::Twine("Operation \"") + name + "\" requires a minimum of " +
1962  llvm::Twine(opMinRegionCount) +
1963  " regions but was built with regions=" + llvm::Twine(*regions))
1964  .str()
1965  .c_str());
1966  }
1967  if (opHasNoVariadicRegions && *regions > opMinRegionCount) {
1968  throw nb::value_error(
1969  (llvm::Twine("Operation \"") + name + "\" requires a maximum of " +
1970  llvm::Twine(opMinRegionCount) +
1971  " regions but was built with regions=" + llvm::Twine(*regions))
1972  .str()
1973  .c_str());
1974  }
1975 
1976  // Unpack results.
1977  std::vector<PyType *> resultTypes;
1978  if (resultTypeList.has_value()) {
1979  populateResultTypes(name, *resultTypeList, resultSegmentSpecObj,
1980  resultSegmentLengths, resultTypes);
1981  }
1982 
1983  // Unpack operands.
1984  llvm::SmallVector<MlirValue, 4> operands;
1985  operands.reserve(operands.size());
1986  if (operandSegmentSpecObj.is_none()) {
1987  // Non-sized operand unpacking.
1988  for (const auto &it : llvm::enumerate(operandList)) {
1989  try {
1990  operands.push_back(getOpResultOrValue(it.value()));
1991  } catch (nb::builtin_exception &err) {
1992  throw nb::value_error((llvm::Twine("Operand ") +
1993  llvm::Twine(it.index()) + " of operation \"" +
1994  name + "\" must be a Value (" + err.what() + ")")
1995  .str()
1996  .c_str());
1997  }
1998  }
1999  } else {
2000  // Sized operand unpacking.
2001  auto operandSegmentSpec = nb::cast<std::vector<int>>(operandSegmentSpecObj);
2002  if (operandSegmentSpec.size() != operandList.size()) {
2003  throw nb::value_error((llvm::Twine("Operation \"") + name +
2004  "\" requires " +
2005  llvm::Twine(operandSegmentSpec.size()) +
2006  "operand segments but was provided " +
2007  llvm::Twine(operandList.size()))
2008  .str()
2009  .c_str());
2010  }
2011  operandSegmentLengths.reserve(operandList.size());
2012  for (const auto &it :
2013  llvm::enumerate(llvm::zip(operandList, operandSegmentSpec))) {
2014  int segmentSpec = std::get<1>(it.value());
2015  if (segmentSpec == 1 || segmentSpec == 0) {
2016  // Unpack unary element.
2017  auto &operand = std::get<0>(it.value());
2018  if (!operand.is_none()) {
2019  try {
2020 
2021  operands.push_back(getOpResultOrValue(operand));
2022  } catch (nb::builtin_exception &err) {
2023  throw nb::value_error((llvm::Twine("Operand ") +
2024  llvm::Twine(it.index()) +
2025  " of operation \"" + name +
2026  "\" must be a Value (" + err.what() + ")")
2027  .str()
2028  .c_str());
2029  }
2030 
2031  operandSegmentLengths.push_back(1);
2032  } else if (segmentSpec == 0) {
2033  // Allowed to be optional.
2034  operandSegmentLengths.push_back(0);
2035  } else {
2036  throw nb::value_error(
2037  (llvm::Twine("Operand ") + llvm::Twine(it.index()) +
2038  " of operation \"" + name +
2039  "\" must be a Value (was None and operand is not optional)")
2040  .str()
2041  .c_str());
2042  }
2043  } else if (segmentSpec == -1) {
2044  // Unpack sequence by appending.
2045  try {
2046  if (std::get<0>(it.value()).is_none()) {
2047  // Treat it as an empty list.
2048  operandSegmentLengths.push_back(0);
2049  } else {
2050  // Unpack the list.
2051  auto segment = nb::cast<nb::sequence>(std::get<0>(it.value()));
2052  for (nb::handle segmentItem : segment) {
2053  operands.push_back(getOpResultOrValue(segmentItem));
2054  }
2055  operandSegmentLengths.push_back(nb::len(segment));
2056  }
2057  } catch (std::exception &err) {
2058  // NOTE: Sloppy to be using a catch-all here, but there are at least
2059  // three different unrelated exceptions that can be thrown in the
2060  // above "casts". Just keep the scope above small and catch them all.
2061  throw nb::value_error((llvm::Twine("Operand ") +
2062  llvm::Twine(it.index()) + " of operation \"" +
2063  name + "\" must be a Sequence of Values (" +
2064  err.what() + ")")
2065  .str()
2066  .c_str());
2067  }
2068  } else {
2069  throw nb::value_error("Unexpected segment spec");
2070  }
2071  }
2072  }
2073 
2074  // Merge operand/result segment lengths into attributes if needed.
2075  if (!operandSegmentLengths.empty() || !resultSegmentLengths.empty()) {
2076  // Dup.
2077  if (attributes) {
2078  attributes = nb::dict(*attributes);
2079  } else {
2080  attributes = nb::dict();
2081  }
2082  if (attributes->contains("resultSegmentSizes") ||
2083  attributes->contains("operandSegmentSizes")) {
2084  throw nb::value_error("Manually setting a 'resultSegmentSizes' or "
2085  "'operandSegmentSizes' attribute is unsupported. "
2086  "Use Operation.create for such low-level access.");
2087  }
2088 
2089  // Add resultSegmentSizes attribute.
2090  if (!resultSegmentLengths.empty()) {
2091  MlirAttribute segmentLengthAttr =
2092  mlirDenseI32ArrayGet(context->get(), resultSegmentLengths.size(),
2093  resultSegmentLengths.data());
2094  (*attributes)["resultSegmentSizes"] =
2095  PyAttribute(context, segmentLengthAttr);
2096  }
2097 
2098  // Add operandSegmentSizes attribute.
2099  if (!operandSegmentLengths.empty()) {
2100  MlirAttribute segmentLengthAttr =
2101  mlirDenseI32ArrayGet(context->get(), operandSegmentLengths.size(),
2102  operandSegmentLengths.data());
2103  (*attributes)["operandSegmentSizes"] =
2104  PyAttribute(context, segmentLengthAttr);
2105  }
2106  }
2107 
2108  // Delegate to create.
2109  return PyOperation::create(name,
2110  /*results=*/std::move(resultTypes),
2111  /*operands=*/std::move(operands),
2112  /*attributes=*/std::move(attributes),
2113  /*successors=*/std::move(successors),
2114  /*regions=*/*regions, location, maybeIp,
2115  !resultTypeList);
2116 }

2143  PyOperation &operation = operationBase.getOperation();
2144  if (operation.isAttached())
2145  throw nb::value_error(
2146  "Attempt to insert operation that is already attached");
2147  block.getParentOperation()->checkValid();

2149  if (refOperation) {
2150  // Insert before operation.

2161  "versus 'InsertionPoint(block)'?");
2162  }
2163  }
2164  mlirBlockInsertOwnedOperationBefore(block.get(), beforeOp, operation);
2165  operation.setAttached();
2166 }

2428 void PySymbolTable::walkSymbolTables(PyOperationBase &from,
2429  bool allSymUsesVisible,
2430  nb::object callback) {
2431  PyOperation &fromOperation = from.getOperation();
2432  fromOperation.checkValid();
2433  struct UserData {
2434  PyMlirContextRef context;
2435  nb::object callback;
2436  bool gotException;
2437  std::string exceptionWhat;
2438  nb::object exceptionType;
2439  };
2440  UserData userData{
2441  fromOperation.getContext(), std::move(callback), false, {}, {}};
2442  mlirSymbolTableWalkSymbolTables(
2443  fromOperation.get(), allSymUsesVisible,
2444  [](MlirOperation foundOp, bool isVisible, void *calleeUserDataVoid) {
2445  UserData *calleeUserData = static_cast<UserData *>(calleeUserDataVoid);
2446  auto pyFoundOp =
2447  PyOperation::forOperation(calleeUserData->context, foundOp);
2448  if (calleeUserData->gotException)
2449  return;
2450  try {
2451  calleeUserData->callback(pyFoundOp.getObject(), isVisible);
2452  } catch (nb::python_error &e) {
2453  calleeUserData->gotException = true;
2454  calleeUserData->exceptionWhat = e.what();
2455  calleeUserData->exceptionType = nb::borrow(e.type());
2456  }
2457  },
2458  static_cast<void *>(&userData));
2459  if (userData.gotException) {
2460  std::string message("Exception raised in callback: ");
2461  message.append(userData.exceptionWhat);
2462  throw std::runtime_error(message);
2463  }
2464 }

2726 /// A list of operation attributes. Can be indexed by name, producing
2727 /// attributes, or by index, producing named attributes.
2728 class PyOpAttributeMap {
2729 public:
2730  PyOpAttributeMap(PyOperationRef operation)
2731  : operation(std::move(operation)) {}
2732 
2733  MlirAttribute dunderGetItemNamed(const std::string &name) {
2734  MlirAttribute attr = mlirOperationGetAttributeByName(operation->get(),
2735  toMlirStringRef(name));
2736  if (mlirAttributeIsNull(attr)) {
2737  throw nb::key_error("attempt to access a non-existent attribute");
2738  }
2739  return attr;
2740  }
2741 
2742  PyNamedAttribute dunderGetItemIndexed(intptr_t index) {
2743  if (index < 0) {
2744  index += dunderLen();
2745  }
2746  if (index < 0 || index >= dunderLen()) {
2747  throw nb::index_error("attempt to access out of bounds attribute");
2748  }
2749  MlirNamedAttribute namedAttr =
2750  mlirOperationGetAttribute(operation->get(), index);
2751  return PyNamedAttribute(
2752  namedAttr.attribute,
2753  std::string(mlirIdentifierStr(namedAttr.name).data,
2754  mlirIdentifierStr(namedAttr.name).length));
2755  }
2756 
2757  void dunderSetItem(const std::string &name, const PyAttribute &attr) {
2758  mlirOperationSetAttributeByName(operation->get(), toMlirStringRef(name),
2759  attr);
2760  }
2761 
2762  void dunderDelItem(const std::string &name) {
2763  int removed = mlirOperationRemoveAttributeByName(operation->get(),
2764  toMlirStringRef(name));
2765  if (!removed)
2766  throw nb::key_error("attempt to delete a non-existent attribute");
2767  }
2768 
2769  intptr_t dunderLen() {
2770  return mlirOperationGetNumAttributes(operation->get());
2771  }
2772 
2773  bool dunderContains(const std::string &name) {
2774  return !mlirAttributeIsNull(mlirOperationGetAttributeByName(
2775  operation->get(), toMlirStringRef(name)));
2776  }
2777 
2778  static void bind(nb::module_ &m) {
2779  nb::class_<PyOpAttributeMap>(m, "OpAttributeMap")
2780  .def("__contains__", &PyOpAttributeMap::dunderContains)
2781  .def("__len__", &PyOpAttributeMap::dunderLen)
2782  .def("__getitem__", &PyOpAttributeMap::dunderGetItemNamed)
2783  .def("__getitem__", &PyOpAttributeMap::dunderGetItemIndexed)
2784  .def("__setitem__", &PyOpAttributeMap::dunderSetItem)
2785  .def("__delitem__", &PyOpAttributeMap::dunderDelItem);
2786  }
2787 
2788 private:
2789  PyOperationRef operation;
2790 };
